    • Method Detail

      • sendTwoStepVerification

        public TwoStepVerificationResponse sendTwoStepVerification(SendTwpStepVerificationParameters parameters)
                                                    throws RouteeAuthenticationException,
                                                           java.io.IOException,
                                                           RouteeTwoStepException
        You can send a 2Step verification very easily just by specifying the recipient, the type of the message and the method that the verification will be sent. The message type that is currently supported is "code" which generates a numeric only code with the specified number of digits. The method that is currently supported is "sms", so the specified recipient must be a valid mobile number. All optional parameters that are required by 2Step are taken from your application settings which can be configured through the Routee web console.
        Parameters:
        parameters - the parameters
        Returns:
        the two step verification response
        Throws:
        RouteeAuthenticationException - the routee authentication exception
        java.io.IOException - Signals that an I/O exception has occurred.
        RouteeTwoStepException - the routee two step exception
